{
  "stem": "9156.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But they wanted that I get a regular passport and that I get into Austria and start working against the Nazis again.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I have to say it wasn't something I looked forward to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I really didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I felt so much the obligation because we all knew that they were terrorists.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As I say, it didn't start with Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I had friends, Jews and non-Jews, who were in Buchenwald-- B-U-C-H-E-N-W-A-L-D.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I haven't seen it, but people came out from there, and they would tell me that this man-- and I forgot his name-- that he had to shovel his grave, and they put him in the grave, and they closed it.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now, we knew that, so we thought we have to continue.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so to get an Austrian passport, I had to marry somebody who was Austrian.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "This is something I don't like to talk about because it wasn't a marriage that had any meaning to me, but that I felt it as a pain.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know, it's not something I like.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I-- that nice lawyer said something good to me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He said, well, in the olden emperors' times, the kings and queens had to marry somebody they didn't care about so that they can be kings and queens.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Nowadays, it's the anti-Nazi underground people who have to do that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was a nice way to say it, but it was terrible because you had to pretend, and I never liked to pretend.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as I say, there was another very dedicated man.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was in Paris.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they asked him, since he was an Austrian, whether he would go back to Czechoslovakia and then Austria and marry this woman just for the paper.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Paul was already in Paris, and we didn't like the idea at all.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
